  <TITLE>Bug: Plus Email Address Not Accepted</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>Version: 0.9.15 Docker When attempting to create a new user that has a &quot;+&quot; in the Email address, an &quot;E-mail must be valid&quot; error is returned. Plus addressing is valid per [RFC 2822](http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2822#section-3.4.1) and is supported by major Email providers such as Gmail and Office 365/Exchange to name a few. **Steps to Replicate** - Open a Project - Click &quot;Team &amp; Auth&quot; - Click &quot;New User&quot; - Attempt to create a user with a &quot;+&quot; in the address, such as &quot;validation+bug@nocodb.com&quot; - Observe the &quot;E-mail must be valid&quot; message **What is Expected?** The Email is valid per RFC spec and should be allowed.</DESCRIPTION>
